At 09:03 PM 05/12/2003, you wrote:

>Does anyone know where I can find a battery terminal like this. It's the
>original kind with the male spade connector for the aux. battery relay wire.

I forgot about the spade. If you replace the terminal with something else, 
you can get a positive cable with a 10 gauge pigtail. Crimp a male spade to 
it, hook up your alternator terminal then insulate the connection with tape 
or shrink wrap.
